The paper deals with the problem of interactive function computation in a differential privacy setting, which involves privacy, information theory, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the optimization of accuracy measures, which involves algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on privacy and accuracy measures could also make cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a relevant sub-category.
